'''Roland Bürger''' (born 1972(?)<ref>[http://www.merkur-online.de/lokales/landkreis-erding/ganz-locker-hitparaden-476053.html Ganz locker in die Hitparaden] {{in lang|de}}, merkur-online, 24 September 2009.</ref>), better known as '''"Bürgermeista"''' is a [[Germany|German]] guitarist and founder of the band ''Bürgermeista & Die Gemeinderäte'' in 2010.<ref>[http://www.ednetz.de/artikel/rgermeista-im-ednetz-interview-01.html/ Video interview at ednetz.de] {{in lang|de}}</ref> "Bürgermeista" is [[Bavarian language|Bavarian]] for ''Bürgermeister'' (mayor), "Gemeinderäte" are the members of a municipal council.
== Career == Bürger originally comes from [[Dorfen]] near [[Munich]]. He was known as a guitarist of several musical groups. In 2008 he wrote the song ''Locker macha'' (Bavarian dialect for "locker machen", ~ loosen up), recorded it together with colleagues as a [[reggae]] song. and sent it to several radio stations. In the summer of 2009, a radio personality of [[Radio Gong 96,3]], a well-known local radio in [[Munich]], played the song in his morning program, and afterwards at the request of listeners frequently in his radio show after June 23, 2009.<ref>[http://www.radiogong.de/artikel/Mike-Thiel-Show/Mike-Thiel-Show/MMMike's+Shitparade/307/ MMMike's Shitparade on Radio Gong] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121028060919/http://www.radiogong.de/artikel/Mike-Thiel-Show/Mike-Thiel-Show/MMMike%27s%2BShitparade/307/ |date=October 28, 2012 }} {{in lang|de}}.</ref> The song became number one of the ''Reggae & Ska'' downloads on [[amazon.com]].<ref>[http://www.bild.de/BILD/regional/muenchen/leute/2009/07/08/sommerhit-des-jahres/ein-buergermeister-rockt-radio-gong.html Ein Bürgermeister rockt Radio Gong] {{in lang|de}}, Bild München, 8 July 2009.</ref> Soon other local radio stations noticed the song, and after Bürger got a record contract at [[313music JWP]].<ref>[https://archive.today/20120910064955/http://www.myschlager.de/schlager/3693-buergermeista-locker-macha.html Info on myschlager.de]</ref><ref>[http://www.bild.de/BILD/regional/muenchen/leute/2009/08/02/buergermeista/locker-macha-roland-buerger-unterschreibt-seinen-plattenvertrag-bei-313jwp.html Plattenvertrag für den Bürgermeista] {{in lang|de}}, Bild München, 2 August 2009.</ref> The song was recorded on video. On 21 August 2009 the song was published on CD, and entered in the [[Media Control Charts|Media Control Top100 Singles Charts]].<ref>[http://www.bild.de/BILD/regional/muenchen/leute/2009/09/02/buergermeista/auf-platz-64-in-den-wiesn-charts.html Platz 64! Jetzt stürmt Bürgermeista die Wiesn] {{in lang|de}}, Bild München, 2 September 2009.</ref> On 4 September 2009, during the [[Oktoberfest]], the song climbed on place 39. Altogether the song was seven weeks on the charts.<ref name="charts">[https://archive.today/20130211153352/http://www.musicline.de/de/chartverfolgung_summary/artist/B%25fcrgermeista/single DE-Chartverfolgung]</ref>
== Discography == === Albums === * ''Gewählt'' (Bürgermeista & die Gemeinderäte, 2010)
=== Singles === * ''Locker macha'' (2009) * ''Guad'' (2009) * ''Do reggae mi ned auf'' (Bürgermeista & die Gemeinderäte, 2010) * ''Heid is da ois is ma Wurst-Dog'' (Bürgermeista & die Gemeinderäte, 2011)
